f Strategic Reviews that forms part of the City Corporation’s Change Programme. It aims to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">obtain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> a better deal on the goods and services and mak</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> savings of £30 million over the next five years and an on-going legacy of £9.4</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">illion per year</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City Corporation is committed to a number of broader initiatives</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. These include a local procurement project, which provides free support for supply chain professionals to encoura</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ge local procurement with SMEs. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">These initiatives are accompanied by a number of practical steps including</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">breaking down contracts into smaller parts to make the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">opportunities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> more attractive and manageable for SMEs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The City Corporation also uses the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> City of London Procurement Charter to encourage City firms and developers to adopt local procurement as part of their </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">corporate social responsibility (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">CSR</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">)</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and business competitiveness agendas.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">To what extent is local government procurement organised to deliver value for money and social, economic and environmental objectives, including stimulating the local economy? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Local Government procurement could be criticised for a perceived lack of flexibility, and for being a drawn</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">-</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">out process.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> This can often lead to a disadvantage in obtaining best value results. The City however has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">sought to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mitigat</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">against </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">any disadvantage </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">through a number of initiatives:</span></li></ol><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">arge</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> suppliers for engagement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">– for example</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> ‘meet the buyer’ where specific procurement issues/opportunities can be addressed;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">adopting</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> pragmatic procurement practices to maximi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e participation such as the early identification of contracts suitable for SME</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s; </span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 46.52pt; padding-left:7.33pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the ability to maintain a flexible approach towards contract award criteria</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 53.85pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> recognise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the value of procuring from SMEs</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he fundamental principles are outlined in the City o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f London’s Procurement Strategy </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">and the City provides online guidance to encourage the use</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> of</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> SMEs and local businesses to stimulate economic regeneration in the supply chain</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">n addition the City of London encourages developers (through inclusion in planning agreements and development of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Local Procurement Charter) to adopt local SME procurement. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he City </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ffers free support to City businesses to encourage local and SME procurement with a ‘Local Toolkit’ designed to offer information </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> small and local businesses and the ‘Ready to Supply the City’ initiative</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which actively works with SMEs to improve their ability to compete for contract opportunities</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The City has been recognised by the Department for Communities and Local Government as one of the “Best Councils to do Business with”.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City of London delivers on its CSR objectives directly and indirectly through its supply chain.  Most recently, in awarding contracts to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mitie</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for Building Repairs and Maintenance and to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Agilisys</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> for IS service provision, a large number of apprenticeships have been created for the benefit of young people.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">To what extent are local authorities achieving the involvement of local residents in delivering value for money? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Compared to conventional local authorities, t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he City of London has very few residents to consult</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">onsultation is typically conducted in conjunction with the application of the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Public Services (</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Social Value</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">) Act 2012, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> part of the Section 20 requirement of the Landlord and Tenant Act 1985, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in connection with</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> works pertaining to residential areas it is engaged </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">as and when appropriate for procurements. The case by case approach adopted by the City of London procurement team provides flexibility to conduct consultation in appropriate levels or forms instead of a blanket approach which can be restrictive in terms of levels and methods of engagement.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">To what extent are local authorities able to develop long-term relationships with contractors?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The building of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">long-term relationships can be difficult</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, although good partnership working can be created through proactive contract management. There is always a risk of investment for the supplier in building relationships as there is no guarantee of extending the relationship to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">future</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> contracts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">not least because </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">contracts need to be advertised </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">in the Official Journal of the European Union (OJEU) according to EU Procurement Directives. T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">his can make parties reluctant to engage in such relationships. However, if successful, relationships can last for a number of years and beyond with consultation, market testing and knowledge. Flexibility in policy and contracts to allow re-negotiation where there are clear and reportable benefits to the public sector and supplier should be considered.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Do authorities take sufficient advantage of collaborative and joint procurement opportunities, including those available from central government? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14pt; padding-left:22pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City takes full advantage of established </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rameworks (e.g. I</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">mprovement and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">fficiency </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">outh </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">E</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ast</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">anaged </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ervices, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">emporary </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">gency and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ecruitment</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, G</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">overnment </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">P</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rocurement </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">S</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ervice</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Frameworks) to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">procure whilst minimis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ing the lengthy process and administration of a typical tender process. As the City of London is relatively small in comparison to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">conventional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">authorities, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">it has </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">work</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> with </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">London Boroughs to provide services together in order to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> deliver</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> economies of scale</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. This has reduced </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">costs and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">encouraged </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">best value, typically in </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ocial </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are as the City has very few residents.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City’s procurement teams are engaged with a number of local networks to discuss and collaborate on projects, as well as sub regional bodies such as the East London </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">lliance. A significant barrier to progress this work is having the dedicated re</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">source </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to focus on these relationships and partnerships between boroughs to ensure continuity, not just for the City but f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">or</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the boroughs. Work could be conducted to review the landscape of procurement over a region and pooling procurements together </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to maximize savings and press for social benefits. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Some organisations may feel their identity is at risk if they collaborate on all levels of procurement.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">More specifically, does local government have sufficient understanding of its procurement expenditure and the markets for goods and services to deliver quality procurement strategies—locally and regionally?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Understanding spend is essential for the development of suitable procurement strategies to meet corporate objectives and obtain value for money</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">his is expected of all local authorities.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Figures for annual spend are shared on the London Contracts Register, as well as figures for spend with local</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> firms</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, SME</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ocial </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nterprise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> which is located on </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">the City’s </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">website</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City has recently </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">centralis</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to form the City of London Procurement Ser</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">vice (CLPS) and has adopted a c</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ategory management approach to focus specific skill sets on</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> relevant target areas of spend. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Managers are required to analyse their</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">spend, identify projects and propose procurement str</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ategies in line with objectives.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">his approach is being more widely adopted across </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">l</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ocal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">uthorities although more work could be done in this area.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">If not, how could deficiencies be addressed?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="14" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">R</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">egional spend</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> could be targeted</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> by concentrating on certain categories of spend that are consistent across all organisations</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">highways, education, financial services </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">– so as to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">develop </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">greater understanding of spend and impact on the community.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">To what extent is risk in local government procurement and contracting understood and managed and contracting strategies adopted, which are tailored to product and supplier market places?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="15" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">There is generally a disconnect with procurement and the team that conduct</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the contract management</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. The purchasers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> will not be the ultimate owners of the risk and as such do not necessarily take this into consideration. However, as previously mentioned</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> the City of London operates a Category </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">anagement Structure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> part of which </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> regular meetings with stakeholders at ‘Category Board </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">M</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">eetings’</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">his allows the procurement team to discuss any topic or potentials risks relevant to the procurement and to agree any mitigation to be incorporated into the procurement strategy. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="16" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">isk </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ppetite of internal customers in the current economic climate is currently </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">low and as a result </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">stakeholders </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are generally </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">less likely to compromise stability and guaranteed continuity of service in order</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> to make CSR benefits. As such r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">isk is high on the agenda </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">local authorit</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ies</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">, sometimes </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">at the expense of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">competition and innovation.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="17" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Regional </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">isk alignment would be desirable</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">D</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">espite efforts to share data on portals such as the London Contracts Register, better use of data and contract management to understand markets, associated risks and requirements is needed to obtain best value.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">More specifically, do local authorities maintain and operate effective client management functions and have they entered contractual arrangements which allow the flexibility to meet changing circumstances such as budget reductions or changes in the way a service has to be delivered?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="18" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City is adopting a new contract management approach to address this</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">. C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ontracts are now handled by the appropriate departments and contracts allow for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">certain amount of reasonable flexibility as determined appropriate for the contract. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How is regularity and propriety of procurement secured and are the arrangements for detecting and addressing impropriety and fraud effective?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Procurement Regulations for the City of London are updated annually to ensure relevance and fitness for purpose. All revision of the regulations and new policy is subject to scrutiny of elected members and senior management to ensure appropriate and realistic targets. Greater planning and monitoring of contracts </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">enables </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">suitable timeframes to be allowed for appropriate tender process. This removes the requirement to have a less then optimal process and compromise value for money or meeting corporate objectives.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Greater transparency and communication of procurements is being planned with the addition of a contracts register to the City of London web page to allow viewers to see how and where funds are spent and when relevant contracts are due for renewal.  A supported </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Whistleblowing</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> Policy and Employee Code of Conduct is in force to report, highlight and control any suspicious or improper action for investigation.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Is local authority procurement fully transparent, audited effectively and does it provide appropriate mechanisms for redress?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">he City has adopted </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a number of practices to ensure its procurement is transparent. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Centralised processes mean that a set structure </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">followed for</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> each procurement with regular i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nternal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">udits to ensure appropriate procedures are followed and identify them if they are not, or conversely improved processes could be adopted.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> The City also encourages full debriefs </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> stimulate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> communications with bidders for feedback on the process</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Data </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">is </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">now being collected on the demographic of bi</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">dders and their success to monitor any</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> potential shortfalls or</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> highlight any areas which the C</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">orporation could look to address and support bidders in future</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 53.85pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Specifically, are the arrangements for securing the accountability of procured services and goods to local authorities and local residents adequate and effective? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="21" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yes, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">rocurements can be traced from concept through to management and at each stage </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> logged an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">d reported on performance with i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">nternal </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">udits scheduled at intervals throughout the year to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">spot check</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">More specifically, to what extent are loca</span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">l authorities able to provide assurance to central government that value for money (in the broadest sense of the term) is delivered?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="22" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20pt; padding-left:16pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">The City of London operates procurement processes with the expectation that there will be a requirement to </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">provide </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">evidence and show a strategic process has been followed (under the confines of EU regulations) to develop best value. This</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> comb</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">ined with regular reporting to elected m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">embers</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> makes the procurement team accountable for the procurement and process and ensure</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> objectives and best value </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">are </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">delivered.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><a href="http://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/business/tenders-and-procurement/sustainable-procurement/Pages/default.aspx"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/business/tenders-and-procurement/sustainable-procurement/Pages/default.aspx</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:10pt"> </span></p></body></html>